    "created_at": "2012-11-09T19:40:42Z",
    "updated_at": "2012-11-09T19:40:42Z",
    "body": "@Blub, this API is intended to be safe, so ARCs make the most sense to me. There is another proposal for adding unsafe globals to the language: #553.\n\nPlain ARCs though have, in theory, no overhead to read, while RWARCs do involve locking.\n\nAlso, global @-pointers would be very unsafe.\n",
    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
