    "created_at": "2012-11-09T21:06:39Z",
    "updated_at": "2012-11-09T21:06:39Z",
    "body": "I don't think global @-pointers are required, but ARCs are read-only, and RWARCs add overhead, this is my main concern. I think this and #553 should go hand in hand: mut-globals which are declared as unsafe should not be RWARC-guarded. I'd really like to use mutable globals, but I would definitely not use RWARCs in my current usecases.\n",
